#: ../../source/checks/fit_utils/fit-coefficients.md:1
msgid "_fit_coefficients"
msgstr "_fit_coefficients"

#: ../../source/checks/fit_utils/fit-coefficients.md:3
msgid "Firma"
msgstr "Signature"

#: ../../source/checks/fit_utils/fit-coefficients.md:13
msgid "Che problema risolve"
msgstr "What problem it solves"

#: ../../source/checks/fit_utils/fit-coefficients.md:15
msgid ""
"Calcola un singolo aggiornamento dei coefficienti del fit lineare pesato: pendenza, intercetta e "
"varianza pesata di `x`."
msgstr ""
"Computes one update of the weighted linear-fit coefficients: slope, intercept, and weighted "
"variance of `x`."

#: ../../source/checks/fit_utils/fit-coefficients.md:17
msgid "Contratto sugli input"
msgstr "Input contract"

#: ../../source/checks/fit_utils/fit-coefficients.md:19
msgid "`x`, `y` e `weights` devono essere gia validati dal chiamante."
msgstr "`x`, `y`, and `weights` must already be validated by the caller."

#: ../../source/checks/fit_utils/fit-coefficients.md:20
msgid "`weights` deve contenere pesi strettamente positivi."
msgstr "`weights` must contain strictly positive weights."

#: ../../source/checks/fit_utils/fit-coefficients.md:21
msgid "`x` deve avere varianza pesata finita e non nulla."
msgstr "`x` must have a finite, non-zero weighted variance."

#: ../../source/checks/fit_utils/fit-coefficients.md:23
msgid "Dove viene usata"
msgstr "Where it is used"

#: ../../source/checks/fit_utils/fit-coefficients.md:25
msgid "in [`lin_fit`](../../moduli/fit_utils/lin-fit.md) per il calcolo iniziale dei coefficienti"
msgstr "in [`lin_fit`](../../moduli/fit_utils/lin-fit.md) for the initial coefficient estimate"

#: ../../source/checks/fit_utils/fit-coefficients.md:26
msgid "in [`lin_fit`](../../moduli/fit_utils/lin-fit.md) a ogni iterazione quando `sigma_x` e presente"
msgstr "in [`lin_fit`](../../moduli/fit_utils/lin-fit.md) at each iteration when `sigma_x` is provided"

#: ../../source/checks/fit_utils/fit-coefficients.md:28
msgid "Come fallisce"
msgstr "Failure modes"

#: ../../source/checks/fit_utils/fit-coefficients.md:30
msgid "`ValueError` se la varianza pesata di `x` non e finita"
msgstr "`ValueError` if the weighted variance of `x` is not finite"

#: ../../source/checks/fit_utils/fit-coefficients.md:31
msgid ""
"`ValueError` se la varianza pesata di `x` e troppo vicina a zero, cioe se non ci sono abbastanza "
"valori distinti per stimare la pendenza"
msgstr ""
"`ValueError` if the weighted variance of `x` is too close to zero, meaning there are not enough "
"distinct values to estimate the slope"

#: ../../source/checks/fit_utils/fit-coefficients.md:33
msgid "Perche resta privata"
msgstr "Why it stays private"

#: ../../source/checks/fit_utils/fit-coefficients.md:35
msgid ""
"E un mattone interno dell'algoritmo di `lin_fit`. Documentarlo chiarisce il flusso del calcolo, "
"ma non avrebbe molto senso come endpoint pubblico separato."
msgstr ""
"It is an internal building block of the `lin_fit` algorithm. Documenting it clarifies the "
"calculation flow, but it would not make much sense as a separate public endpoint."

